data.title: Nick Booker-Brown - 2023 UTSA Football Roster
data.meta_description: 2023 UTSA Football Roster - Nick Booker-Brown: The official athletics website for the UTSA Roadrunners.
data.text:
Sophomore (2022)

Honorable Mention All-Conference USA performer at defensive end in his first season with the Roadrunners … played in 13 games and drew four starts … posted 28 total tackles, eight solo stops, six tackles for loss, three sacks, two pass breakups, one quarterback hurry and a forced fumble … made his UTSA debut in the 41-38 overtime win at Army, registering three tackles including a sack for a 5-yard loss … made a season-high six stops, including 2.5 TFLs and a sack in the 30-10 road triumph over FIU … had three tackles, including a sack, and forced a fumble in the 44-38 double-overtime win at UAB … recorded three stops with one behind the line of scrimmage in the 41-7 victory at Rice … also had three tackles and a QB pressure in the 34-31 comeback win against UTEP.

Prior to UTSA

Transfer from NC State … played in five games as a true freshman in 2020 … recorded a pair of tackles, including one for a loss of five yards … two-time first-team all-district performer on the defensive line at Westfield High School for head coach Matt Meekins … Touchdown Club of Houston Defensive Player of the Year finalist … named second-team All-Greater Houston Area by the Houston Chronicle … helped the Mustangs to a 13-2 record, including a perfect 7-0 mark in district action, and to the Class 6A Division II state semifinals as a senior … three-star prep prospect … also played basketball.

Personal

Born April 16, 2001 … older brother Josh was a linebacker at UTSA in 2017 and also played at Boise State, where he was named the Broncos' defensive scout MVP while redshirting in 2019 … multidisciplinary studies major.
